This is StoryQuest, a web-based D&D-inspired RPG with an LLM-powered Dungeon Master.

- Use Typescript with strict type checking.
- Backend: Node.js with Express.js, PostgreSQL for data.
- Frontend: React.js with Redux for state management.
- Integrate LLM via a dedicated service (e.g., OpenAI GPT).
- Use Cucumber for BDD tests, organized by feature modules.
- Write unit tests with Jest for backend and frontend.
- Secure endpoints with JWT authentication.
- Follow RESTful API conventions.
- Use ESLint and Prettier for code consistency.
- Validate and sanitize all user inputs.
- Optimize LLM context for narrative coherence.
- Comment code clearly and update README regularly.
- Use Git with feature branches and meaningful commits.
- Set up CI/CD for testing and deployment. 